other_tests.findings: Fluid-filled dilated (8-9 mm) appendix with slight wall enhancement, minimal periappendiceal fat stranding, no adjacent fluid collections, and slight thickening at the cecal base and proximal ascending colon. There is a hypodensity in the left kidney likely representing a simple cyst. No significant retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
other_tests.changes_over_time: A fluid density mass at the level of the takeoff has minimally increased in size since examination ___ years prior, likely representing a small lymphocele or gastrointestinal duplication cyst.
